-- BC Partners Agrees to Buy Allflex From Electra for $1.3 Billion
-- B y   E d w a r d   E v a n s
-- 2013-05-03T10:43:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-03/bc-partners-agrees-to-buy-allflex-from-electra-for-1-3-billion.html
BC Partners Ltd., a London-based
private-equity firm, agreed to buy Allflex Holdings in a deal
valuing the maker of identity tags for animals at about $1.3
billion, including debt.  Electra will reap about $398 million in gross proceeds from
the sale, the seller said in a statement today. Electra had
valued Allflex, its largest investment, at about 154 million
pounds ($240 million) as of Sept. 30.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Edward Evans in London at 
